-Richard Feynman posses a unique quality among Nobel Prize winners in Physics - he was the only to publicly admit that he regularly hallucinates. He was also the only who didn&#8217;t put his light-protective glasses on when one of his collaborative projects – the atomic bomb. Feynman will be an inspirational example of the theoretical ideas presented above. This is his autobiography.</p>

<p>If you feel like you something is preventing you from achieving your goals this should be placed at the top of your reading list. For those who already know a little bit about what I&#8217;m talking about, continue your process of self-discovery and self-examination.</p>

<p>I want you all to be happy. I want you all to succeed. Becoming at peace with yourself is an incredibly important part. The engineering skill-set is incredibly important as well, but it is almost impossible to take advantage of that in a creative way until you are at peace, or beginning to achieve peace with yourself.</p>

